-- Mizuho says VP Hayashi to replace Sato as Mizuho Bank president
-- By Taiga Uranaka
-- Thu Jan 23, 2014 01:48AM EST
-- None



TOKYO, Jan 23 (Reuters) - Mizuho Financial Group Inc <8411.T> said on Thursday that Vice President Nobuhide Hayashi will take over as president of core unit Mizuho Bank effective April 1.

Current President Yasuhiro Sato will remain head of Mizuho Financial Group, Japan's second-biggest bank said. Mizuho will hold a news conference at 4:30 p.m. (0730 GMT) regarding the management changes.